│ The comparison is `fcmp une <denormal_val>, 0.0`.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is that the constant folding logic for `fcmp` does not correctly handle denormal floating-point numbers when the `"denormal-fp-math"` attribute is `"ieee,dynamic"`. The     │
│ `dynamic` part is key: it means the denormal handling mode can change at runtime, so compile-time optimizations cannot assume a fixed mode (like flush-to-zero).                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The folding happens in `ConstantFoldCompareInst`. This function calls `APFloat::compare`. The `APFloat` comparison logic needs to be aware of the denormal handling mode.                │
