│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The call chain is roughly `SimplifyFCmpInst` -> `ConstantFoldCompareInst`. `SimplifyFCmpInst` has access to the instruction, and thus the function and its attributes.                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to check for the `"denormal-fp-math"` attribute in `SimplifyFCmpInst`. If the mode is `"ieee,dynamic"`, and either of the constant operands is a denormal number, we should   │
│ bail out of constant folding, as we cannot be sure about the runtime behavior.                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify `SimplifyFCmpInst` in `lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp`. I'll add a check at the beginning of the function. If the operands are constants, I'll check if they are     │
│ denormal. If so, and if the function has `"denormal-fp-math"="ieee,dynamic"`, I will return `nullptr` to prevent folding.                                                                │
